'''The camel's nose''' is a metaphor for a situation where the permitting of some small act will lead consequently to a larger undesireable act or circumstance.

The root phrase usually attributed to be a saying of arabs, or middle eastern cultures, roughtly as follows:
:''Do not allow a camel put his nose under the edge of your tent, for soon you will have a camel in your tent.''

